{"id":290727434,"lang":"python3","time":"1 year, 6 months","timestamp":1578029807,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"5220 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/290727434/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Perfect Squares","memory":"13 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def numSquares(self, n: int) -> int:\n        max_num = int(n**(1/2))\n        prev = list(range(n+1))\n        \n        for num in range(1, max_num+1):\n            sq = num**2\n            current = [None] * (n+1)\n            \n            for i in range(n+1):\n                if i < sq:\n                    current[i] = prev[i]\n                else:\n                    current[i] = min(prev[i], current[i-sq]+1)\n            prev = current\n        return prev[-1]","compare_result":"","title_slug":"perfect-squares"}
